law.text:
Each application for involuntary admission to a facility or Veterans' Administration hospital under Part III of this subtitle shall:
Be in writing;
Be dated;
Be on the form required by:
The Administration, in the case of a facility; or
The Veterans' Administration hospital, in the case of a Veterans' Administration hospital;
State the relationship of the applicant to the individual for whom admission is sought;
Be signed by the applicant;
Be accompanied by the certificates of:
1 physician and 1 psychologist; or
2 physicians; and
Contain any other information that the Administration requires.
